article.headline: North Texas 79, Southern U. 58
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Collin Dennis scored 16 points to help North Texas stay unbeaten at home in a 79-58 win over Southern University on Monday night. Ben Bell scored 12 points and Keith Wooden added 10 for North Texas (7-2), which has now started a season 5-0 at home for the first time since 1977. Steffon Wiley led Southern (1-8) with 15 points. Dennis, Bell and Wooden shot a combined 16-of-19 from the field, and Quincy Williams scored 10 points to reach double figures for the fourth straight game. North Texas trailed by as much as 15 early before ending the first half on a 39-13 run.
